  "prompt": "Can i send my GRE scores to the four universities freely?",
  "response": "When you take the GRE, you typically have the option to send your scores to up to four graduate programs for free at the time of taking the test. After that, if you want to send your scores to additional universities, you will have to pay a fee for each additional score report sent. It's important to check with the specific universities regarding their individual requirements for GRE scores and whether they accept the scores directly from ETS, as some may have different policies.",
